# Week 1 — Command Line Navigation & File Management
 
Codecademy – Learn the Command Line

## Objective
Gain foundational proficiency in Linux command-line navigation and file management to prepare for system administration and cloud computing tasks.

---

## Skills Learned
- Navigating the Linux filesystem using absolute and relative paths
- Listing and organizing files and directories
- Viewing and reading file contents directly from the terminal
- Moving, renaming, copy and deleting files and directories
- Understanding how to combine commands with options and arguments

---

## Commands Practiced

| Command | Description | Example |
|---------|-------------|---------|
| `pwd`   | Displays the current working directory | `pwd` |
| `ls`    | Lists files and directories | `ls -la` |
| `cd`    | Changes the working directory | `cd /home/user/Documents` |
| `mkdir` | Creates a new directory | `mkdir projects` |
| `touch` | Creates a new empty file | `touch notes.txt` |
| `cat`   | Displays the content of a file | `cat notes.txt` |
| `mv`    | Moves or renames files/directories | `mv notes.txt archive/` |
| `rm`    | Deletes files | `rm oldfile.txt` | rm -r Deletes Directories
| 'cp'    | Copy files | cp file1 file2 destination_folder
Learned list 'ls' command options 
|ls -a| lists all contents, including hidden files and directories.
|ls -l| lists all contents, in long format.
|ls -t| lists all contents, by the time they were last modified.
